The species has a wide distribution in Brazil , registered in the Amazon and Atlantic forest. Probably this apparently disjunct distribution is a reflection of the studies focusing on chironomid fauna performed in these two biomes, which does not happen in the intermediate areas, consisting of the Cerrado, Caatinga and Pantanal (see discussion in
Pinho et al. 2009
). Future collections in these poorly sampled areas could help us to better understand the distribution of this and other chironomid species.
